Since the year 2010, the percent of wealth in the United States that is held by the wealthiest 1% has followed the formula [`p=0.34(n-2010)+28.3`] where [`n`] is the year. If you want to know when the top 1% held [$p]% of the wealth, you have the equation [`[$left]=[$right]\text{.}`] Does this happen in the year [`[$proposed_solution]\text{?}`]

>> [@DataTable(
  [
    [PGML('[`[$left->TeX]`]'),
     PGML('[`=`]'),
     PGML('[`[$right->TeX]`]'),
    ],
    [PGML('[`[$lefteval->TeX]`]'),
     PGML('[`\wonder{=}`]'),
     PGML('[_]{$righteval}{3}'),
    ],
  ],
      align => 'rcl',
      valign => 'middle',);@]* <<

[_]{$dropdown}{5}

